main event: Two disc-shaped objects were observed making rapid maneuvers over Edwards AFB, California, on May 29, 1952.
interesting points: The objects demonstrated unusual performance characteristics that differed from known aircraft., The observed speed of the objects was between 400 and 500 knots., The sighting was made by 7 technical personnel considered reliable observers., The weather conditions during the sighting were excellent, with visibility of 20 miles., No physical evidence or known meteorological conditions accounted for the sighting.
